"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750379","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-18","<p>Data on the value of UK exports of goods and services to the EU countries and the rest of the world are available from the Office for National Statistics (ONS) at the following link (Table 3):</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/file?uri=/economy/nationalaccounts/balanceofpayments/adhocs/006656balanceofpaymentsannualgeographicaldatatables/2015updateddetailedgeographictradedata.xls" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/file?uri=/economy/nationalaccounts/balanceofpayments/adhocs/006656balanceofpaymentsannualgeographicaldatatables/2015updateddetailedgeographictradedata.xls</a></p><p>Source: ONS Balance of Payments annual geographical data tables.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-07-18T16:41:42.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750379/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750379/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750379/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-10","Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the total value of exports of goods and services was to (a) countries comprising the EU single market and (b) the rest of the world in each of the last 10 years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Kate Hoey","Vauxhall","Kate Hoey","3747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750380","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Department for International Trade has not cancelled any contracts put out to tender since July 2016. One contract has been re-tendered.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-18T10:57:41.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750380/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750380/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750380/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-10","Department for International Trade: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many contracts put out to tender by his Department have been (a) cancelled and (b) re-tendered since his Department's creation.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750381","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-14","<p>The proportion of public procurement contracts awarded through framework agreements by the Department for International Trade, since July 2016 is 80%.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-14T11:50:40.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750381/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750381/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750381/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-10","Department for International Trade: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what proportion of public procurement contracts his Department awarded through framework agreements since his Department's creation.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750382","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-18","<p>Since July 2016, the Department has led 51 trade missions to key markets across the world covering over 19 sectors, with an average number of 15 delegates per mission. My Rt. Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade accompanied the Prime Minister with a business delegation to India in November 2016.</p><p>The Department for International Trade Ministers undertook 134 visits in the Department’s first year; 97 were overseas, underlining the Department’s commitment to helping British companies win business in international markets.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-07-18T16:47:35.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750382/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750382/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750382/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-10","Department for International Trade: Trade Promotion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many trade delegates he has led since taking up his position; and to which countries he has led those delegates.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","4096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750383","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-18","<p>As set out in the policy paper “Safeguarding the position of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU”, family members of eligible EU citizens resident in the UK before we leave the EU will also be able to apply for settled status after five years provided they meet the criteria. Those joining after our exit will be subject to to the same rules that currently apply to non-EU nationals joining British citizens, or alternatively to future immigration arrangements.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-18T11:11:07.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750383/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750383/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750383/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 5 July 2017 to Question 2279, on immigration: EU nationals, what the Government's policy is on the status of partners of EU citizens from non-EU countries residing in the UK on a visa sponsored by an EU citizen with permanent residency as set out in the Immigration Rules.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750384","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union has cancelled one contract since it was formed on 14 July 2016, no contracts have been retendered.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-18T16:25:51.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750384/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750384/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750384/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Department for Exiting the European Union: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many contracts put out to tender by his Department have been (a) cancelled and (b) re-tendered in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750385","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-13","<p>The list of sectors that we have been examining will be published shortly. Parliament has agreed that we will not publish anything that would undermine the Government’s ability to negotiate the best deal for Britain, and our commitment to publication does not mean that we have changed our position on revealing information which may harm our negotiating position.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-13T15:54:00.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750385/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750385/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750385/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 26 June 2017 to Question 239, on what dates he plans to release the list of sectors his Department has been examining.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","3781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750386","Home Office","false","2017-07-13","<p>Applicants for settled status after EU exit will not be required to pass a citizenship test.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-13T16:55:08.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750386/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750386/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-10","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to paragraph 6 of her Department's policy paper, Safeguarding the position of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, whether applicants for settled status will be required to pass the citizenship test.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","3782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750387","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-13","<p>While the UK remains a member of the European Union, the EU must continue to honour the rights and legal obligations of UK nationals resident in the EU, under EU Treaties.</p><p>The government has been clear that we want to reach a reciprocal agreement for EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU as quickly as possible.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-13T14:23:52.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750387/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750387/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","British Nationals Abroad: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to his Department's policy paper, Safeguarding the position of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, what his policy is on the legal status of UK nationals residing in other EU member states in the context of the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","3786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750388","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-13","<p>EU citizens who obtain settled status and remain resident in the UK will have no immigration conditions placed on their residence in the UK, be able to work or study here freely, live permanently in the UK with a partner who has settled status or is a UK national, and have access to benefits and public services in line with UK nationals.</p><p>The proposed arrangements will be enshrined in UK law and enforceable through the UK judicial system, up to and including the Supreme Court. We are also ready to make commitments in the Withdrawal Agreement which will have the status of international law.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-13T14:41:20.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750388/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750388/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to paragraph 6 of his Department's policy paper, Safeguarding the position of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, whether the rights accrued by those who obtain settled status in the UK will be for life.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","3787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750389","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-18","<p>Since the Department for Exiting the European Union was established, 75% of contracts over £10k have been awarded via framework agreements.</p><p>Government departments are required to publish details of contracts awarded over £10k. We have excluded lower value contracts under this threshold from the response as the administration with tracking contracts of low value can only be achieved at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-18T16:31:30.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750389/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750389/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Department for Exiting the European Union: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of procurement contracts were awarded through framework agreements by his Department since it was established.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750390","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union does not hold this information centrally. It is the Department’s commercial policy to compete requirements wherever this is possible in order to be able to realise best value for money. Depending on the size of the procurement, a range of methodologies are used including the sourcing of three or more quotes, government frameworks, or an open competitive tender.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-18T16:29:02.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750390/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750390/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Department for Exiting the European Union: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many bids were on average received for each contract put out to tender by his Department since it was established.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750391","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-17","<p>As part of the exit negotiations, the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue cooperation in the work of the European Observatory on the supply of medical radioisotopes in the best interests of both the UK and the EU.</p><p>It is notable that Euratom places no restrictions on the export of medical radioisotopes to countries outside the EU - they are not subject to Euratom Supply Agency contracts or to Euratom safeguards.</p><p>As we set out in our White paper, ‘The United Kingdom’s exit from and new partnership with the European Union’, we would welcome agreement to continue to collaborate with our European partners on major science, research, and technology initiatives.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-17T14:53:25.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750391/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750391/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","European Observatory on the Supply of Medical Radioisotopes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether it is the Government's policy to remain part of the European Observatory on the supply of medical radioisotopes.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","4043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750392","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-18","<p>We will be asking EU citizens to make an application to the Home Office for documentation demonstrating their new settled status in due course. This process will be as streamlined as possible for all individuals, whether that be new applicants or those who already hold a residence document under current free movement rules.</p><p>Anyone who would like to find out the latest information, including when they will need to sign up for the new scheme, can sign-up for email updates here: <a href="https://gov.smartwebportal.co.uk/homeoffice/public/webform.asp?id=67&amp;id2=627DF7&amp;active=True" target="_blank">https://gov.smartwebportal.co.uk/homeoffice/public/webform.asp?id=67&amp;id2=627DF7&amp;active=True</a></p><p><br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-18T11:12:50.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750392/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750392/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 5 July 2017 to Question 2279, on immigration: EU nationals, whether the process will differ for people (a) with permanent residence applying for a grant of settled status and (b) submitting new applications to reside in the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750393","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-13","<p>While the UK will maintain an interest, any decision on official languages of the EU after the UK’s withdrawal will be one to be taken by the EU institutions and their Member States.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-13T15:57:02.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750393/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750393/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-10","European Union: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the English language would cease to be an official language of the EU after the UK's withdrawal from the EU.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","3894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750901","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The outcomes we are trying to achieve for the South Eastern franchise were stated in the public consultation document. We want more reliable services, longer trains and better customer service.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation has now closed and we are reviewing the responses. We will ensure the next franchise delivers the services that passengers want.</p><p> </p><p>On 22<sup>nd</sup> June my Department announced the four companies who expressed an interest in operating the service from December 2018.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T11:50:34.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750901/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750901/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750901/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made towards an outcome for the Southeastern franchise.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","900465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751586","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The benefits of franchising to passengers and taxpayers are clear. The private sector have invested billions in new trains. Government subsidy to the industry has reduced by £2.5bn over ten years. Whilst passenger numbers have doubled since privatisation.</p><p> </p><p>All this is on top of our ongoing £38bn investment in infrastructure. We always assess franchising decisions against the best interests of passengers and taxpayers.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T15:33:46.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751586/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751586/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751586/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Railways: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the costs and benefits of rail franchising.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","900473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751587","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>Electrification of the Great Western Mainline between Paddington and Maidenhead has been successfully delivered. This has enabled a peak hours electric service to be introduced between Maidenhead and Paddington on 22nd May this year, with more services introduced on 3 July.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As a result the first Turbo trains have been cascaded to the West of England, which also started operation on 3 July, providing a 35% increase in capacity on the Severn Beach Line and better passenger facilities providing early benefits to Bristol.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T16:06:29.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751587/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751587/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751587/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Great Western Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress he has made on the electrification of the Great Western main line.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","900470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751588","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Government will be publishing its air quality plan to tackle nitrogen dioxide emissions by the end of July. We also intend to publish our emissions reduction plan - setting out how we will reduce carbon emissions through the 2020s – once Parliament returns after the summer recess.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-13T15:58:27.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751588/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751588/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751588/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to reduce the level of emissions from road transport.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","900469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751589","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>Any change to the speed limit would have to be based on a full and sound understanding of the wider safety, environmental and other impacts of such a change.</p><p> </p><p>A previous Government made an initial assessment of the possibility of introducing trials of 80 mph limits. A decision on whether to change the limit would be for this Government but we currently have no plans to do so.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-13T14:55:46.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751589/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751589/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751589/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Motorways: Speed Limits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department is taking steps to increase the national speed limit on motorways.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","900474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751590","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>Departmental officials are in discussion with Nexus, the Tyne and Wear Metro, regarding their proposals for new rolling stock.</p><p> </p><p>Any decision will need to represent value for money and be affordable given the funding was not included in the Department’s Spending Review settlement in 2015.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-13T15:18:19.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751590/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751590/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751590/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Tyne and Wear Metro: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to make a decision on the new fleet for the Tyne and Wear Metro.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","900467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751591","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Department supports the need for the capacity improvements that Crossrail 2 could bring to London and the wider South East. We are currently analysing the business case to ensure it is a robust investment with a credible funding plan. Our next steps to deliver those capacity improvements will be decided when that analysis is complete.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T15:55:23.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751591/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751591/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751591/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to make a decision on the Crossrail 2 business case; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","900472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749613","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-13","<p>In 2014-15, Central Government spent over £12 billion (27.1%) with small and medium sized businesses, which shows a continued year on year increase in SMEs winning public procurements; and we are committed to increasing spend with them through public procurement.</p><p> </p><p>Information on all public sector suppliers within a specific constituency is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-13T10:58:01.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749613/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749613/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749613/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-07","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the (a) amount and (b) proportion of public procurement placed with small and medium-sized businesses in (i) Oxford city, (ii) Oxford West and Abingdon constituency and (iii) Oxfordshire in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","3673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749614","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-12","<p>Projected savings were outlined in the Summer Budget 2015. Over the parliament 2010-2015, the government’s firm restraint over public sector pay delivered reductions to departmental spending, saving approximately £8 billion.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-12T14:04:23.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749614/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749614/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749614/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-07","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much has been saved in 2017 prices as a result of the imposition of the public sector pay cap.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","3645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749615","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-12","<p>According to the Office for Budget Responsibility’s Spring Budget 2017 forecast, the Government is forecast to spend 10.9% of GDP in 2017/18 on welfare in the United Kingdom. This figure falls to 10.7% in 2018/19, 10.5% in 2019/20 and 10.3% in 2020/21 and 2021/22.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-12T09:29:11.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749615/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749615/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749615/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-07","Social Security Benefits: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much he plans to spend on social security in each of the next five financial years as a percentage of gross domestic product.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","3655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749616","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government is committed to maintaining transparency about its procurement activity and publishes information about its contracts with a value of over £10,000 on the “Contracts Finder” website. The information requested is readily available here: https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","3607","2017-07-12T10:27:05.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749616/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749616/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749616/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-07","Treasury: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many contracts have been awarded by or on behalf of his Department to (a) Brewin Dolphin PLC, (b) Tullett Prebon PLC, (c) PARC, (d) Oxera, (e) Goodacre UK, (f) RELX, (g) Royal Dutch Shell, (h) KPMG, (i) Lloyds, (j) Bishop Fleming Accountants, (k) Ernst & Young, (l) Clerical Medical, (m) Heathrow Airport, (n) Deloitte, (o) PwC, (p) Grant Thornton and (q) Slaughter & May since July 2015; and what the value was of each of those contracts.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749617","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government is committed to maintaining transparency about its procurement activity and publishes information about its contracts with a value of over £10,000 on the “Contracts Finder” website. The information requested is readily available here: https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","3606","2017-07-12T10:27:05.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749617/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749617/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749617/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-07","Treasury: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many contracts have been awarded by or on behalf of his Department to (a) Brewin Dolphin PLC, (b) Tullett Prebon PLC, (c) PARC, (d) Oxera, (e) Goodacre UK, (f) RELX, (g) Royal Dutch Shell, (h) KPMG, (i) Lloyds, (j) Bishop Fleming Accountants, (k) Ernst & Young, (l) Clerical Medical, (m) Heathrow Airport, (n) Deloitte, (o) PwC, (p) Grant Thornton and (q) Slaughter & May between July 2010 and July 2015; and what the value was of each of those contracts.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749618","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-14","<p>Given the breadth and depth of the UK-US relationship, there are regular discussions between UK Ministers and their US counterparts on economic and other issues – including on US trade and steel. Global overcapacity in steel and other sectors has also been discussed regularly with international partners, including at the G7 and G20 Summit.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-14T12:11:24.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749618/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749618/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-07","Iron and Steel: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he last discussed with members of the US Cabinet trade in steel between the US and the UK.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","3621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749619","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government takes the threat of pension scams very seriously.</p><p> </p><p>That is why the Government launched a consultation in December 2016 looking at three potential interventions to tackle this issue, including legislating to introduce a ban on cold calling in relation to pensions to help stop fraudsters contacting individuals and legislating to give firms new powers to block transfers. The government will publish a response to the consultation which will set out our intended next steps. This is a complex area that requires careful and detailed consultation with stakeholders.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman","3625","2017-07-17T13:53:35.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749619/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749619/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-07","Nuisance Calls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the timetable is for the introduction of legislative proposals on banning pension cold-calling and blocking suspicious pension pot transfers.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","3624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749620","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-24","<p>Licensing is an effective targeted tool delivering improved standards and safety in the private rented sector in specific areas that are suffering from serious problems.</p><p>In April 2015 further conditions for applying selective licensing were introduced, so local authorities could target defined areas with problems such as deprivation, high crime and poor property.</p><p>Any scheme submitted to the Secretary of State for confirmation will be considered on its merits and whether it meets the statutory requirements in Part 3 of the Housing Act 2004.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-24T15:46:07.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749620/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749620/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Private Rented Housing: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effect of borough-wide licensing schemes in raising standards and improving safety in the private rented sector.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","3654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749621","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-13","<p>In 2014 the Government took action to cap repair charges imposed on leaseholders by public sector landlords for government-funded maintenance. In addition, since 2014 all property managing agents in England must belong to one of three approved redress schemes, allowing consumers to follow up complaints and drive up standards with the least regulatory burden. The Government has no plans to regulate leaseholders’ maintenance fees.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-13T15:25:47.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749621/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749621/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will introduce regulations on the level of maintenance fees borne by leaseholders.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749622","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-19","<p>Where following an inspection of dwelling under the Housing Act 2004, a local authority identifies polystyrene ceiling tiles as being a fire risk, an Improvement Notice can be served requiring their removal. Failure to comply with an Improvement Notice is a criminal offence for which local authorities can impose a financial penalty of up to £30,000 and apply for a Rent Repayment Order covering up to 12 month’s rent, or prosecute in the courts which have the power to impose an unlimited fine.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-19T14:14:21.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749622/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749622/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749622/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Buildings: Fire Hazards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 29 June 2017 to Question 371, whether there is a requirement to remove polystyrene ceiling tiles from older buildings.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","3678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749623","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-14","<p>The number of local authority dwellings sold by local authority is published in live table 648: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-social-housing-sales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-social-housing-sales</a></p><p>Figures are not collected at a constituency level.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-14T11:17:30.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749623/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749623/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749623/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749623/answer/previousversion/3960","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Council Housing: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many council homes have been sold in (a) Ashford constituency and (b) Nottingham in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","3706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749624","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-18","<p>Where work is necessary to ensure the fire safety of social housing, we will ensure that lack of financial resources will not prevent them going ahead.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-18T16:11:57.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749624/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749624/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749624/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749624/answer/previousversion/3917","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will set out the criteria against which applications for additional funding from local authorities for work to address fire safety in tower blocks will be assessed.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","3700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749625","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-25","<p>The Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government made a statement on 5 July setting out that the Grenfell Tower Recovery Taskforce will consider all aspects of the recovery operation, but will have a special focus on housing, regeneration and community engagement. The Recovery Taskforce will advise, support and challenge the Council, and will report to the Secretary of State directly.</p><p>The Taskforce is set up as a non-Statutory Intervention to work with the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea - following their request for support from central government - on the longer term recovery following the Grenfell Tower disaster. Commissioners, on the other hand, are appointed by the Secretary of State to exercise specific functions of an authority where he is satisfied that the authority is failing to comply with its Best Value Duty (Local Government Act 1999).</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","3701","2017-07-25T14:01:09.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749625/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749625/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749625/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749625/answer/previousversion/3959","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Kensington and Chelsea Borough Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, for what reasons he appointed a recovery taskforce for the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea Council and not Commissioners; and how the powers, responsibilities and accountability of that taskforce differ from those of Commissioners.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","3702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749626","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-25","<p>The Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government made a statement on 5 July setting out that the Grenfell Tower Recovery Taskforce will consider all aspects of the recovery operation, but will have a special focus on housing, regeneration and community engagement. The Recovery Taskforce will advise, support and challenge the Council, and will report to the Secretary of State directly.</p><p>The Taskforce is set up as a non-Statutory Intervention to work with the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea - following their request for support from central government - on the longer term recovery following the Grenfell Tower disaster. Commissioners, on the other hand, are appointed by the Secretary of State to exercise specific functions of an authority where he is satisfied that the authority is failing to comply with its Best Value Duty (Local Government Act 1999).</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","3702","2017-07-25T14:01:09.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749626/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749626/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749626/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749626/answer/previousversion/3958","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Kensington and Chelsea Borough Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will set out the powers, scope, responsibilities and accountability of the recovery taskforce appointed to run the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","3701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749627","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>The Housing White Paper reflects our ambition to support local authorities in building more affordable homes. My officials are working with local authorities to understand all the options for increasing the supply of affordable housing, considering innovative ideas and bespoke deals with local authorities to support delivery.</p><p>We have made £7.1 billion available through the Shared Ownership and Affordable Homes Programme 2016-2021. Local authorities can bid for this to fund a range of schemes. Local authorities can also work with the Homes and Communities Agency to access the Starter Homes Land Fund, to prepare brownfield sites that will include a high proportion of starter homes and other affordable homeownership tenures. We have also provided £32 million of Estates Regeneration grant funding, to assist with the early stages of regeneration schemes that offer the potential to deliver new homes.</p><p>Planning policy already makes it clear that local authorities should plan to meet the market and affordable housing needs in their area, insofar as possible. In doing so we expect them to work with their local communities to decide how much housing is necessary, of what type and where it should go.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-20T16:44:54.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749627/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749627/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749627/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749627/answer/previousversion/3961","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-07","Council Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what incentives are available to local authorities to build council housing on (a) brownfield and (b) greenfield sites.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","3707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749628","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-12","<p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published quarterly on the Gov.uk website at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dcms-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-1-january-to-31-march-2017</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-12T16:29:11.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749628/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749628/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749628/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","S4C","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what meetings (a) she and (b) Ministers of her Department have had with representatives of S4C since 1 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","3697"
