"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749630","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-12","<p>Government believes everyone should have access to opportunities in the cultural sectors. Ministers and officials across the Department regularly meet with a range of representatives of the performing arts industry to discuss issues affecting the sector, including the issue of diversity. The Government is clear that it expects the cultural sectors to represent our diverse society in their artistic talent, workforce and audiences.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-07-12T10:11:02.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749630/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749630/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749630/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","Performing Arts: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions she has had with representatives of the performing arts industry on diversity in casting voice-only performances.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","3699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749631","Home Office","false","2017-07-12","<p>This Government has been clear there should be no safe space online for terrorists and their supporters to radicalise, recruit, incite, or inspire. In March 2017, the Home Secretary held a very positive meeting with industry to discuss online terrorist content. Subsequent to the roundtable, Google, Facebook, Twitter and Microsoft made a public commitment to look at options for establishing an industry-led forum focused on tackling terrorist and extremist content online.</p><p>This was formally announced by the companies on 26 June 2016. We continue to work closely with industry to come up with new, innovative ways for tackling terrorist use of the internet but, as the Prime Minister has made clear, we will also explore the possibility of creating legal requirements for communications service providers if they fail to take the necessary action to remove unacceptable content</p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-07-12T15:37:26.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749631/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749631/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749631/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-07","Social Media: Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to introduce fines for social media companies which fail to remove extremist content from their platforms.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","3681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749632","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-13","<p>We regularly meet major social media companies to discuss online harm and other issues.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","3682 ; 3683 ; 3684","2017-07-13T08:02:59.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749632/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749632/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749632/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","Social Media: Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions she has had with social media companies to ensure that they comply with their terms of service on removing offensive content including hate speech from their platforms.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","3685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749634","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-13","<p>We regularly meet major social media companies to discuss online harm and other issues.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","3683 ; 3684 ; 3685","2017-07-13T08:02:58.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749634/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749634/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749634/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","Social Media: Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with social media companies on the adoption of a consistent approach to reporting and removing hate speech across all platforms.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","3682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749635","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-17","<p>As set out in previous statements to the House, the Secretary of State's quasi-judicial responsibilities in relation to the proposed acquisition of Sky by 21st Century Fox will be discharged thoroughly, robustly and transparently. Such decisions must also be taken as promptly as is reasonably practicable.</p><p>On 29 June the Secretary of State announced that she is minded-to refer the merger to the Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) on media plurality grounds. In coming to a final decision, consideration will be given to the available evidence before her including any further representations received following the call for evidence which closed on 14 July.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-17T14:31:47.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749635/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749635/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749635/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","21st Century Fox: Sky","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if she will postpone any decision on the proposed takeover of Sky by 21st Century Fox until after the publication of any report on the second stage of the Leveson Inquiry.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","3669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749636","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-13","<p>We regularly meet major social media companies to discuss online harm and other issues.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","3682 ; 3684 ; 3685","2017-07-13T08:02:58.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749636/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749636/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749636/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","Social Media: Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions she has had with social media companies on educating their employees on (a) antisemitic, (b) Islamophobic and (c) racist images or discourse on their platforms.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","3683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749637","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-13","<p>We regularly meet major social media companies to discuss online harm and other issues.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","3682 ; 3683 ; 3685","2017-07-13T08:02:58.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749637/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749637/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749637/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","Social Media: Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with social media companies to agree a single working definition of hate crime between all platforms.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","3684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749638","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-17","<p>The department has regular discussions with the Welsh Office on a range of issues, including the S4C review.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-17T14:17:26.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749638/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749638/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749638/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","S4C Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Wales on whether devolution of broadcasting should be included in the remit of the S4C review.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","3620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749639","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-19","<p>Directors of organisations responsible for making unsolicited marketing calls should be held to account. We intend to consult over the summer on making the necessary changes to the Privacy and Electronic Communication Regulations 2003, with a view to introducing the legislation by the end of the year.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-19T13:11:54.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749639/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749639/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749639/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","Privacy and Electronic Communications (EC Directive) Regulations 2003","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what the timetable is for the consultation on amending the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulation 2003 to introduce director liability for breaches of that regulation.","false","Biography information for Patricia Gibson","North Ayrshire and Arran","Patricia Gibson","3632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749640","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-17","<p>The government is committed to carrying out a review of S4C's remit, governance and funding in 2017. The full scope of the review will be set out in the terms of reference in due course.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-17T14:15:14.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749640/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749640/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749640/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-07","S4C Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if she will include the devolution of broadcasting in the remit of the S4C review.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","3619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749641","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-14","<p>I am unable to comment on the work currently under way to ensure any new housing contract proves better value for the Department as to do so would prejudice the Department's commercial interests. There is a break clause to allow for re-negotiation of the contract with Annington Homes Limited in 2021.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-14T12:49:37.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749641/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749641/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749641/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-07","Annington Homes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the implications for the public purse of Annington's 2021 review of rents on the properties sold to it by his Department in 1996; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","3649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749642","Department for Education","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Department for Education recognises the value of international exchange and collaboration in education, as part of our vision for the UK as a global nation. We will consider participation in European programmes as part of the negotiation.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-07-17T11:22:54.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749642/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749642/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749642/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-07","Erasmus+ Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to maintain the UK's involvement in the Erasmus scheme after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","3679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749643","Department for Education","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Department does not hold the information you have requested.</p><p>The Department only holds data on the number of pupils in independent alternative provision (AP) that have been commissioned by local authorities. This is available in the Schools, Pupils and their Characteristics Statistical First Release which can be accessed at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2017</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-17T16:11:26.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749643/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749643/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749643/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-07","Private Education: Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children in each local authority and constituency are registered in independent alternative provision for excluded young people; how many of those children are (a) enrolled or (b) being directed offsite for their education there for more than one day a week in each year since 2010; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","3659"
