"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749350","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-14","<p>There were approximately 1,400 Defence personnel working in direct support of Operation Temperer following its activation on the 23 May 2017. Approximately 980 of those were military personnel and 390 were Ministry of Defence Police, who deployed in support of the Police. The remaining personnel, a combination of both civilian and military, were supporting the Headquarters elements.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-14T10:55:14.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749350/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749350/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749350/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel from his Department supported the (a) civilian and (b) military components of Operation Temperer following the activation of that operation on 23 May 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749351","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>We are currently compiling the costs of Operation TEMPERER in conjunction with the Home Office. Once complete a full response will follow, a copy of which will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-11T15:09:44.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749351/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749351/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749351/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what financial resources the Government committed to support the (a) civilian and (b) military components of Operation Temperer following the activation of that operation on 23 May 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749352","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-12","<p>As at 1 April 2017 the UK Armed Forces has 60 Chinooks, all of which are meeting their operational taskings. I am withholding a further breakdown of aircraft status, as its disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-12T14:19:32.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749352/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749352/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749352/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Chinook Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many aircraft in the RAF Chinook helicopter fleet are (a) operational and (b) in storage.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749353","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to him on 27 January 2017 by the then Minister for Defence Veterans, Reserves and Personnel (Mark Lancaster) to Question 60906.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-12T14:37:24.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749353/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749353/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749353/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Low Flying: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has paid in compensation to complainants affected by low-flying aircraft in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749354","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-12","<p>Defence Equipment and Support has Command Acquisition Support Plans in place with each of the Commands. These set out equipment and support requirements over a 10-year period and are reviewed annually.</p>","Livingston","Hannah Bardell",,"2017-07-12T14:24:35.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749354/answer","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749354/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749354/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Defence Equipment: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what command acquisition and support plans for equipment and support requirements are in place between (a) Navy Command, (b) Army Command, (c) Air Command, (d) Joint Forces Commands and Defence Equipment and Support.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749355","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-14","<p>Operation Temperer utilises pre-identified personnel who are held at varying levels of readiness and is designed to limit the impact on personnel. As such, there was no need to cancel any leave during this period of activation.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-14T10:54:37.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749355/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749355/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749355/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel from his Department who support the (a) civilian and (b) military components of Operation Temperer had leave cancelled during the period of the operation's activation from 23 May 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749356","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-13","<p>The information on the number of successful prosecutions there have been for unauthorised entries to military bases in the last two years is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-13T13:21:21.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749356/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749356/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749356/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-06","Military Bases: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many successful prosecutions there have been for unauthorised entries to military bases in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3573"
