"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749386","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-12","<p>The FCO does not have a single Marketing and Advertising department and so does not collate social media spend in a way that would able us to fully answer your request without exceeding the appropriate cost and time limit.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-12T13:34:03.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749386/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749386/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-06","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much his Department has spent on advertising on social media in each month since January 2016.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","3408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749387","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-14","<p>We monitor the situation closely and encourage Turkey to ensure the full protection of fundamental rights, including freedom of expression. Freedom of the media remains a priority for our bilateral projects in Turkey.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-14T13:49:52.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749387/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749387/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-06","Turkey: Mass Media and Press Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the levels of media freedom and plurality in Turkey.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","3474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749388","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-14","<p>The Prime Minister has raised the detention with President Erdogan, at the G20 on 7/8 July, emphasising the importance of fully respecting fundamental rights and the rule of law.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-14T13:48:23.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749388/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749388/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-06","Idil Eser","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has plans to make representations to his counterpart in Turkey on the arrest of Idil Eser, director of Amnesty International, Turkey.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","3477"
