"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749439","Home Office","false","2017-07-11","<p>The commencement of sections 80 to 83 of the Policing and Crime Act 2017 - which amend sections 135 and 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983 - is being aligned with the making of related regulations on the use of police stations as places of safety for adults. These regulations are currently being finalised and will be laid in Parliament as soon as possible thereafter.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-11T15:51:50.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749439/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749439/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-06","Police Custody: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she expects to commence sections 80 to 83 of the Policing and Crime Act 2017.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","3536"
