"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749441","Home Office","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Government is committed to strengthening the UK's response to bribery, corruption, money laundering, fraud and other forms of economic crime.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to review options to improve the effectiveness of the UK's response to economic crime, and any measures resulting from this work will be announced in due course.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-07-11T12:32:21.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749441/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749441/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-06","National Crime Agency: Serious Fraud Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to incorporate the National Crime Agency and the Serious Fraud Office.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","3306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749442","Home Office","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Government is considering a broad range of options to optimise the protection of critical infrastructure such as nuclear sites and railways, including the future roles of the Civil Nuclear Constabulary, the Ministry of Defence Police and the British Transport Police.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-11T15:26:15.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749442/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749442/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-06","Police: Mergers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans the Government has to merge the Civil Nuclear Constabulary, the Ministry of Defence Police and the British Transport Police.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","3307"
